   A Boeing 747 traveling from San
Francisco hit heavy air turbulence en route to Sydney on Sunday,
injuring 22 passengers and two crew members, officials said.
   Most of the victims aboard the Qantas Airways flight suffered
neck injuries and abrasions and were rushed by ambulances at
