<HEAD>Man Arrested On Murder Charge Seven Years After Paperwork Mixup</HEAD>
<DATELINE>ST. PETERSBURG, Fla. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   A man was charged with killing an
81-year-old widow seven years after the crime because the paperwork
for his arrest apparently was misplaced.
   The body of Anna Jordon was found Feb. 5, 1981. She had been
raped, beaten and strangled and her 19-inch black-and-white
television set was stolen, police said.
   Rickie Eugene Brown, 28, was held without bond over the weekend
on a first-degree murder charge.
   Brown's stepfather, Larry Donnell Brown, has been on death row
in connection with Mrs. Jordan's murder since 1982. An accomplice,
George Dudley, received a life sentence after testifying that
Rickie Brown raped Mrs. Jordan and Larry Brown killed her.
   Police and prosecutors said they were surprised a warrant had
never been issued for Rickie Brown. The oversight was discovered
recently and St. Petersburg police began looking for him a week ago.
   After he was picked up, Detective Ralph Pflieger said Brown
admitted breaking into the woman's cottage and raping her.
