<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
   The ``preppie'' killer who strangled a young
woman in Central Park was videotaped at a party shortly before his
trial frolicking with several scantily clad female friends and
acting out two strangulations, according to a television news
program.
   The videotape, obtained by ``A Current Affair,'' a nationally
syndicated news program, was made at a late-night party in a
Manhattan apartment last December about the time a jury was being
selected for Robert Chambers' trial, said Rafael Abramovitz, a
reporter-producer on the show.
